pageContext.claim: “The European Union wants to import more liquefied natural gas -- LNG -- from the United States, and they're going to be a very, very big buyer.”
pageContext.analysis: Experts are doubtful. Demand for U.S. LNG in Europe remains limited because of supply from Russian and Norwegian pipelines. The most lucrative markets for U.S. LNG are in South and Central America, India and the Far East.
